content: **The proposed piping and heat exchanger system is designed to cool pavements. It consists of a pump drawing cold water from a lake, a strainer for removing dust, valves to regulate the flow of water, and a flow meter for measuring the flow. Temperature sensors are placed at the inlet and exit of the heat exchanger to measure the water temperature before and after it absorbs heat from the pavement. After heating the water, it is returned to the lake through the exit pipe, creating a closed-loop system that monitors the temperature of the pavement and adjusts the flow of water accordingly.** - <@974165331046170665> (fast)
